# type(scope): subject ← max 72 chars, imperative mood, no period

#

# Types:

# feat → new content or feature

# fix → corrects an error or broken content

# docs → documentation / README changes only

# style → formatting, whitespace, no logic change

# refactor → restructure without adding/fixing

# test → add or update JS test scripts for mongosh

# chore → build, .gitignore, config, tooling

# ci → CI/CD workflow changes

# perf → performance improvements

# revert → revert a previous commit

#

# Scopes (examples):

# week-01 week-07 week-24

# teoria practicas proyecto assets

# glosario recursos rubrica

# scripts docs config

#

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# What? — What was changed? (be specific)

#

# For? — Why? What's the motivation / context?

#

# Impact? — Side effects, breaking changes, dependencies, notes?

#

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Examples:

#

# feat(week-01): add intro theory on MongoDB and NoSQL

#

# What? Add 01-intro-mongodb.md with document model concepts

# For? Students need foundation before running first queries

# Impact? None — new file, no breaking changes

#

# ─────

#

# fix(week-03): correct operator in $elemMatch exercise step 2

#

# What? Fix wrong field name in starter/ejercicio.js

# For? Field mismatch caused mongosh error on execution

# Impact? Minimal — only affects starter file
